agency_name: UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
agency_desc: Oversees federal governmental programs for health and human services.
site_name: HEALTHCARE.GOV - DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
service_description: Provides a website and toll-free phone line for learning about and applying for coverage within the Health Insurance Marketplace established by the Affordable Care Act. Income-eligible Hoosiers may qualify for subsidized health insurance coverage through one of the Marketplace plans.
site_details: Visit website or call to apply.
site_schedule: Phone/Website: Daily 24 hours -- Annual Open Enrollment: Nov 1-Dec 15 -- Special Enrollment Period (for those at or below 150% of the Federal Poverty Level): March 18-Dec 31, 2022
site_eligibility: For enrollment: Under age 65 -- Not eligible for Medicaid, Medicare, or Healthy Indiana Plan (HIP), which generally translates to over 100% Federal Poverty Level for adults and over 250% for minors with additional guidelines for pregnant women, seniors, and persons with disabilities -- US citizens or legal residents -- Not currently incarcerated For reduced premiums (subsidies): Meeting all of the above requirements, plus: Household income at or below 400% Federal Poverty Level -- Not eligible for job-based insurance (or insurance available through employer does not meet affordability or coverage guidelines; call or visit website for details)
